The paper deals with the problem of testing properties of Boolean functions, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The use of Fourier analysis and the focus on testing the correlation of a function with a junta suggest that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The use of distance parameters and the focus on testing suggest that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also possible categories. Finally, the use of Fourier analysis as a main tool suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible category.
